Basically write a DMA list into main RAM,
start the DMA in parallel which will read from main RAM,
write to chip RAM (pipelined [read-ahead] for high utilisation,
however Display DMA and Audio DMA will steal chip RAM cycles,
giving the CPU those cycles in main RAM.)


Affine mappings include scales, rotations, translations, and shears;
they are linear mappings plus a translation.

Geometrically, the vectors (a,d) and (b,e) are basis vectors
of the destination space, and (c,f) is the origin.

Affine mappings can map any triangle in source space into any triangle in destination space,
or map a source rectangle into a destination parallelogram, but no more general distortions are
possible. To warp a rectangle into a general quadrilateral, we will need bilinear.
